      "content": "i get the official docs say its just telemetry but the timing is too precise. it feels programmed to match specific biological frequencies or something. i've seen people on certain forums saying that the way these updates bypass the standard sandbox is to get direct access to the hardware layer for scanning. if you look at the way the packets are structured, they dont look like standard error reports... they look like they're carrying heavy payloads of unstructured data. dont you think it's weird how much more aggressive the data collection has become since the last kernel patch?",
